The launch of the new R1.9-billion Cecilia Makiwane Hospital in the heart of Mdantsane has been described as a giant step towards providing superb healthcare. Eastern Cape premier Phumulo Masualle officially opened the 560-bed hospital next to the old Cecilia Makiwane Hospital yesterday, This hospital compares with the best you can find in the country, he said. Once everything is fully operational, it s going to bring quite a world of difference to the people of Mdantsane, he said.The hospital is expected to begin operating in the next two months.